# User Input in SwiftUI - Interactive Controls

## 1. Understanding State & Binding (60 min)

### The Foundation of SwiftUI Interaction
- **@State**: For local view state that changes over time
- **@Binding**: Creates two-way connection between parent and child views
- **@StateObject**: For reference types that conform to ObservableObject
- **@Published**: Marks properties that should trigger view updates

### State Management Basics:
```swift
struct ContentView: View {
    @State private var username = ""
    @State private var isOn = false

    var body: some View {
        VStack {
            Text("Hello, \(username)!")
            Toggle("Active", isOn: $isOn)
        }
    }
}
```

### Real-world Analogy:
- **@State**: Like your personal notebook - you control what's written
- **@Binding**: Like a shared whiteboard - multiple people can read and write
- **ObservableObject**: Like a company announcement board - everyone gets updates

## 2. Buttons & Actions (45 min)

### Basic Button Syntax:
```swift
Button("Tap Me!") {
    print("Button was tapped!")
}

// With custom styling
Button(action: {
    // Action code here
}) {
    Text("Custom Button")
        .padding()
        .background(Color.blue)
        .foregroundColor(.white)
        .cornerRadius(8)
}
```

### Button Styles & Variations:
```swift
// Different button styles
VStack {
    Button("Plain Style") { }
        .buttonStyle(PlainButtonStyle())

    Button("Bordered") { }
        .buttonStyle(.bordered)

    Button("Bordered Prominent") { }
        .buttonStyle(.borderedProminent)

    Button("Destructive") { }
        .buttonStyle(.borderedProminent)
        .tint(.red)
}
```

### Advanced Button Features:
```swift
// Button with role
Button("Delete", role: .destructive) {
    deleteItem()
}

// Disabled state
Button("Submit") {
    submitForm()
}
.disabled(username.isEmpty)

// Button with system icon
Button {
    shareContent()
} label: {
    Label("Share", systemImage: "square.and.arrow.up")
}
```

## 3. Text Fields & Text Editors (60 min)

### Basic Text Input:
```swift
struct LoginView: View {
    @State private var email = ""
    @State private var password = ""

    var body: some View {
        Form {
            TextField("Email address", text: $email)
                .textContentType(.emailAddress)
                .keyboardType(.emailAddress)
                .autocapitalization(.none)

            SecureField("Password", text: $password)
                .textContentType(.password)
        }
    }
}
```

### Text Field Modifiers & Validation:
```swift
TextField("Username", text: $username)
    .textFieldStyle(.roundedBorder)
    .disableAutocorrection(true)
    .textInputAutocapitalization(.never)
    .onSubmit {
        validateUsername()
    }
    .onChange(of: username) { newValue in
        // React to text changes
        if newValue.count > 20 {
            username = String(newValue.prefix(20))
        }
    }
```

### Text Editor for Multi-line Input:
```swift
struct NoteView: View {
    @State private var noteText = "Enter your notes here..."

    var body: some View {
        TextEditor(text: $noteText)
            .font(.body)
            .lineSpacing(5)
            .border(Color.gray, width: 1)
            .frame(height: 200)
    }
}
```

### Input Formatting & Masks:
```swift
TextField("Phone Number", text: $phoneNumber)
    .keyboardType(.phonePad)
    .onChange(of: phoneNumber) { newValue in
        // Simple phone number formatting
        let filtered = newValue.filter { $0.isNumber }
        if filtered.count <= 10 {
            phoneNumber = formatPhoneNumber(filtered)
        }
    }
```

## 4. Pickers & Selection Controls (60 min)

### Segmented Picker:
```swift
struct ThemePicker: View {
    @State private var selectedTheme = 0
    let themes = ["Light", "Dark", "Auto"]

    var body: some View {
        Picker("Theme", selection: $selectedTheme) {
            ForEach(0..<themes.count, id: \.self) { index in
                Text(themes[index]).tag(index)
            }
        }
        .pickerStyle(.segmented)
    }
}
```

### Wheel & Menu Pickers:
```swift
// Wheel picker
Picker("Select Age", selection: $selectedAge) {
    ForEach(0..<100, id: \.self) { age in
        Text("\(age) years").tag(age)
    }
}
.pickerStyle(.wheel)

// Menu picker (dropdown)
Picker("Color Theme", selection: $selectedColor) {
    Text("Red").tag(Color.red)
    Text("Green").tag(Color.green)
    Text("Blue").tag(Color.blue)
}
.pickerStyle(.menu)
```

### Toggle Switches:
```swift
struct SettingsView: View {
    @State private var notificationsEnabled = true
    @State private var darkMode = false
    @State private var autoPlay = false

    var body: some View {
        Form {
            Toggle("Enable Notifications", isOn: $notificationsEnabled)
            Toggle("Dark Mode", isOn: $darkMode)
            Toggle("Auto-play Videos", isOn: $autoPlay)
        }
    }
}
```

### Stepper & Slider Controls:
```swift
VStack {
    Stepper("Age: \(age)", value: $age, in: 0...120)

    Slider(value: $volume, in: 0...1) {
        Text("Volume")
    } minimumValueLabel: {
        Image(systemName: "speaker.fill")
    } maximumValueLabel: {
        Image(systemName: "speaker.wave.3.fill")
    }

    Text("Volume: \(Int(volume * 100))%")
}
```

## 5. Forms & Data Validation (45 min)

### Building Forms:
```swift
struct RegistrationView: View {
    @State private var firstName = ""
    @State private var lastName = ""
    @State private var email = ""
    @State private var birthDate = Date()
    @State private var receiveNewsletter = true

    var body: some View {
        NavigationView {
            Form {
                Section(header: Text("Personal Information")) {
                    TextField("First Name", text: $firstName)
                    TextField("Last Name", text: $lastName)
                    DatePicker("Birth Date", selection: $birthDate, displayedComponents: .date)
                }

                Section(header: Text("Contact")) {
                    TextField("Email", text: $email)
                        .keyboardType(.emailAddress)
                    Toggle("Receive Newsletter", isOn: $receiveNewsletter)
                }

                Section {
                    Button("Create Account") {
                        registerUser()
                    }
                    .disabled(!isFormValid)
                }
            }
            .navigationTitle("Registration")
        }
    }

    var isFormValid: Bool {
        !firstName.isEmpty && !lastName.isEmpty && !email.isEmpty
    }
}
```

### Input Validation & Feedback:
```swift
TextField("Email", text: $email)
    .onChange(of: email) { _ in
        validateEmail()
    }
    .overlay(
        Group {
            if showEmailError {
                Image(systemName: "exclamationmark.triangle.fill")
                    .foregroundColor(.red)
                    .offset(x: -10)
            }
        },
        alignment: .trailing
    )
```

### Custom Input Styles:
```swift
// Custom text field style
struct RoundedTextFieldStyle: TextFieldStyle {
    func _body(configuration: TextField<Self._Label>) -> some View {
        configuration
            .padding(10)
            .background(Color(.systemGray6))
            .cornerRadius(8)
            .overlay(
                RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 8)
                    .stroke(Color.blue, lineWidth: 1)
            )
    }
}

// Usage
TextField("Search...", text: $searchText)
    .textFieldStyle(RoundedTextFieldStyle())
```

## 6. Advanced Input Patterns (30 min)

### Custom Bindings:
```swift
// Custom binding with validation
var validatedEmail: Binding<String> {
    Binding(
        get: { self.email },
        set: { newValue in
            // Only allow valid email characters
            let filtered = newValue.filter { $0.isLetter || $0.isNumber || "@.-_".contains($0) }
            self.email = String(filtered.prefix(50))
        }
    )
}

TextField("Email", text: validatedEmail)
```

### Focus Management:
```swift
struct LoginForm: View {
    @State private var username = ""
    @State private var password = ""
    @FocusState private var focusedField: Field?

    enum Field {
        case username, password
    }

    var body: some View {
        Form {
            TextField("Username", text: $username)
                .focused($focusedField, equals: .username)
                .submitLabel(.next)
                .onSubmit {
                    focusedField = .password
                }

            SecureField("Password", text: $password)
                .focused($focusedField, equals: .password)
                .submitLabel(.done)
        }
        .onAppear {
            focusedField = .username
        }
    }
}
```

### Input Accessibility:
```swift
TextField("Name", text: $name)
    .accessibilityLabel("Full name")
    .accessibilityHint("Enter your first and last name")
    .accessibilityValue(name.isEmpty ? "Empty" : name)

Button("Submit") { submit() }
    .accessibilityLabel("Submit form")
    .accessibilityHint("Double tap to complete registration")
```

## Best Practices & Common Patterns

### Do's and Don'ts:
- **DO** use appropriate keyboard types for different input types
- **DO** validate input as users type with `.onChange`
- **DO** provide clear feedback for invalid input
- **DON'T** store sensitive data in @State without encryption
- **DON'T** forget to handle different screen sizes and orientations
- **DO** use `.focused` and `@FocusState` for form navigation

### Performance Tips:
- Use `.onChange` sparingly with expensive operations
- Consider debouncing rapid input changes
- Use `@StateObject` for complex validation logic
- Implement custom bindings for input formatting

Complete all practice exercises to master SwiftUI user input controls!"

