# Building Your First iOS App - Todo List (5 hours)

## 1. iOS App Architecture & Setup (60 min)

### Understanding MVC (Model-View-Controller)
- **Model**: Data and business logic (Todo items)
- **View**: User interface elements (Table, buttons, text fields)
- **Controller**: Mediates between Model and View (ViewController)

### Xcode Workspace Tour
- **Project Navigator**: File organization
- **Interface Builder**: Visual UI design
- **Code Editor**: Swift programming
- **Utilities Panel**: Properties and connections

### Creating Your First Project
1. Open Xcode â†’ "Create New Project"
2. Choose "iOS" â†’ "App" template
3. Name: "MyTodoList"
4. Interface: "Storyboard"
5. Language: "Swift"

## 2. Building the User Interface (60 min)

### Storyboard Fundamentals
- **View Controllers**: Screens of your app
- **Views**: UI components (buttons, labels, tables)
- **Auto Layout**: Responsive design for all screen sizes

### Key UI Components for Todo App
```swift
// UITableView - displays list of todos
// UIButton - add new todos
// UITextField - input for new todos
// UINavigationController - navigation between screens
```

### Auto Layout Constraints
- **Leading/Trailing**: Horizontal spacing
- **Top/Bottom**: Vertical spacing
- **Width/Height**: Size constraints
- **Aspect Ratio**: Proportional sizing

## 3. Model: Data Structure (45 min)

### Designing the Todo Model
```swift
struct TodoItem {
    let id: UUID
    var title: String
    var isCompleted: Bool
    var createdAt: Date
    var priority: Priority
}

enum Priority: String, CaseIterable {
    case low = "Low"
    case medium = "Medium"
    case high = "High"
}
```

### Data Persistence Options
- **UserDefaults**: Simple key-value storage
- **Codable + FileManager**: JSON file storage
- **Core Data**: Advanced database (future topic)

### Model Management
```swift
class TodoManager {
    private var todos: [TodoItem] = []

    func addTodo(_ title: String, priority: Priority = .medium) { ... }
    func toggleComplete(_ id: UUID) { ... }
    func deleteTodo(_ id: UUID) { ... }
    func getTodos() -> [TodoItem] { ... }
}
```

## 4. View Controller & Data Binding (60 min)

### ViewController Lifecycle
```swift
class TodoViewController: UIViewController {
    override func viewDidLoad() { 
        // Called once when view loads
    }

    override func viewWillAppear() { 
        // Called before view appears
    }

    override func viewDidAppear() { 
        // Called after view appears
    }
}
```

### UITableView DataSource & Delegate
```swift
// Required methods:
func tableView(_ tableView: UITableView, numberOfRowsInSection section: Int) -> Int
func tableView(_ tableView: UITableView, cellForRowAt indexPath: IndexPath) -> UITableViewCell

// Optional methods:
func tableView(_ tableView: UITableView, didSelectRowAt indexPath: IndexPath)
func tableView(_ tableView: UITableView, commit editingStyle: UITableViewCell.EditingStyle, forRowAt indexPath: IndexPath)
```

### Custom Table View Cells
- Create subclass of UITableViewCell
- Design layout in Interface Builder
- Connect UI elements via @IBOutlet
- Configure cell with model data

## 5. User Interactions & Events (45 min)

### Handling Button Taps
```swift
@IBAction func addButtonTapped(_ sender: UIButton) {
    // Handle add todo action
}
```

### Text Field Delegates
```swift
func textFieldShouldReturn(_ textField: UITextField) -> Bool {
    textField.resignFirstResponder() // Dismiss keyboard
    return true
}
```

### Gesture Recognizers
- **Tap**: Single finger tap
- **Swipe**: Left/right swipe actions
- **Long Press**: Extended touch

### Table View Swipe Actions
```swift
func tableView(_ tableView: UITableView, 
               trailingSwipeActionsConfigurationForRowAt indexPath: IndexPath) -> UISwipeActionsConfiguration?
```

## 6. Data Persistence & State Management (45 min)

### Saving Data with UserDefaults
```swift
// Saving
let encoder = JSONEncoder()
if let encoded = try? encoder.encode(todos) {
    UserDefaults.standard.set(encoded, forKey: "todos")
}

// Loading
if let savedData = UserDefaults.standard.data(forKey: "todos") {
    let decoder = JSONDecoder()
    if let loadedTodos = try? decoder.decode([TodoItem].self, from: savedData) {
        todos = loadedTodos
    }
}
```

### State Restoration
- Save app state when backgrounded
- Restore state when app relaunches
- Handle app termination gracefully

### Error Handling
```swift
do {
    try saveTodos()
} catch {
    showErrorAlert(message: "Failed to save todos")
}
```

## 7. Polish & Final Touches (30 min)

### User Experience Improvements
- **Empty State**: Show message when no todos
- **Loading States**: Activity indicators
- **Error Messages**: User-friendly alerts
- **Haptic Feedback**: Tactile responses

### Accessibility Features
- **VoiceOver**: Screen reader support
- **Dynamic Type**: Adjustable text sizes
- **Color Contrast**: Readable color schemes

### App Icon & Launch Screen
- Design app icon in different sizes
- Create simple launch screen
- Test on various devices

## Best Practices Summary

1. **Keep MVC separation clean**
2. **Use meaningful variable names**
3. **Handle all error cases**
4. **Test on different screen sizes**
5. **Follow iOS Human Interface Guidelines**

You now have all the knowledge to build a complete, functional todo list app!

