# Modifiers & Styling - Custom View Design

## 1. Understanding Modifiers (60 min)

### What are Modifiers?
- Methods that **wrap and transform** views
- Return **new views** with applied changes
- Can be **chained** together
- Enable **consistent styling** across your app

### Basic Modifier Examples:
```swift
Text("Hello SwiftUI")
    .font(.title)           // Font modifier
    .foregroundColor(.blue) // Color modifier
    .padding()              // Layout modifier
    .background(Color.yellow) // Background modifier
```

### Modifier Order Matters:
```swift
// Different order = different results
Text("Example")
    .padding()
    .background(Color.red)  // Background includes padding

Text("Example")
    .background(Color.red)  // Background only on text
    .padding()
```

### Common Built-in Modifiers:
- **Layout**: `.padding()`, `.frame()`, `.position()`
- **Text**: `.font()`, `.foregroundColor()`, `.lineLimit()`
- **Visual**: `.background()`, `.cornerRadius()`, `.shadow()`
- **Interaction**: `.onTapGesture()`, `.gesture()`

## 2. View Composition Patterns (60 min)

### Extracting Subviews:
```swift
// BEFORE: Everything in one view
struct ContentView: View {
    var body: some View {
        VStack {
            Text("Welcome")
                .font(.largeTitle)
                .foregroundColor(.blue)

            Text("Subtitle")
                .font(.subheadline)
                .foregroundColor(.gray)
        }
    }
}

// AFTER: Extracted subview
struct HeaderView: View {
    let title: String
    let subtitle: String

    var body: some View {
        VStack {
            Text(title)
                .font(.largeTitle)
                .foregroundColor(.blue)

            Text(subtitle)
                .font(.subheadline)
                .foregroundColor(.gray)
        }
    }
}

struct ContentView: View {
    var body: some View {
        HeaderView(title: "Welcome", subtitle: "Subtitle")
    }
}
```

### ViewBuilder for Complex Composition:
```swift
struct CardView<Content: View>: View {
    let content: Content

    init(@ViewBuilder content: () -> Content) {
        self.content = content()
    }

    var body: some View {
        content
            .padding()
            .background(Color.white)
            .cornerRadius(10)
            .shadow(radius: 5)
    }
}

// Usage
CardView {
    VStack {
        Text("Title")
        Text("Description")
        Button("Action") { }
    }
}
```

## 3. Creating Custom Modifiers (90 min)

### Basic Custom Modifier:
```swift
struct PrimaryButtonStyle: ViewModifier {
    func body(content: Content) -> some View {
        content
            .foregroundColor(.white)
            .padding()
            .background(Color.blue)
            .cornerRadius(8)
    }
}

// Extension for easier usage
extension View {
    func primaryButtonStyle() -> some View {
        self.modifier(PrimaryButtonStyle())
    }
}

// Usage
Button("Tap Me") { }
    .primaryButtonStyle()
```

### Parameterized Custom Modifiers:
```swift
struct BorderedModifier: ViewModifier {
    let color: Color
    let lineWidth: CGFloat

    func body(content: Content) -> some View {
        content
            .padding(4)
            .overlay(
                RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 8)
                    .stroke(color, lineWidth: lineWidth)
            )
    }
}

extension View {
    func bordered(color: Color = .blue, lineWidth: CGFloat = 1) -> some View {
        self.modifier(BorderedModifier(color: color, lineWidth: lineWidth))
    }
}

// Usage
Text("Bordered Text")
    .bordered(color: .red, lineWidth: 2)
```

### Conditional Modifiers:
```swift
struct ConditionalBackground: ViewModifier {
    let condition: Bool

    func body(content: Content) -> some View {
        if condition {
            content
                .background(Color.yellow)
        } else {
            content
        }
    }
}

extension View {
    func conditionalBackground(_ condition: Bool) -> some View {
        self.modifier(ConditionalBackground(condition: condition))
    }
}
```

## 4. Advanced Styling Techniques (60 min)

### Gradient Backgrounds:
```swift
struct GradientBackground: ViewModifier {
    let colors: [Color]

    func body(content: Content) -> some View {
        content
            .background(
                LinearGradient(
                    gradient: Gradient(colors: colors),
                    startPoint: .topLeading,
                    endPoint: .bottomTrailing
                )
            )
    }
}
```

### Animated Modifiers:
```swift
struct PulseAnimation: ViewModifier {
    @State private var isPulsing = false

    func body(content: Content) -> some View {
        content
            .scaleEffect(isPulsing ? 1.1 : 1.0)
            .animation(
                Animation.easeInOut(duration: 1.0).repeatForever(autoreverses: true),
                value: isPulsing
            )
            .onAppear {
                isPulsing = true
            }
    }
}
```

### Shadow and Depth Effects:
```swift
struct DepthShadow: ViewModifier {
    let intensity: CGFloat

    func body(content: Content) -> some View {
        content
            .shadow(
                color: .black.opacity(0.2 * Double(intensity)),
                radius: 5 * intensity,
                x: 0,
                y: 2 * intensity
            )
    }
}
```

## 5. Building Design Systems (60 min)

### Color Theme System:
```swift
struct AppColors {
    static let primary = Color.blue
    static let secondary = Color.orange
    static let background = Color(.systemBackground)
    static let textPrimary = Color.primary
    static let textSecondary = Color.secondary
}

struct Theme {
    static let cornerRadius: CGFloat = 8
    static let padding: CGFloat = 16
    static let shadowRadius: CGFloat = 4
}
```

### Typography System:
```swift
struct AppFonts {
    static let largeTitle = Font.largeTitle.weight(.bold)
    static let title = Font.title2.weight(.semibold)
    static let body = Font.body
    static let caption = Font.caption
}

// Usage
Text("Heading")
    .font(AppFonts.title)
    .foregroundColor(AppColors.textPrimary)
```

### Complete Component Library:
```swift
struct PrimaryButton: View {
    let title: String
    let action: () -> Void

    var body: some View {
        Button(title, action: action)
            .primaryButtonStyle()
    }
}

struct Card<Content: View>: View {
    let content: Content

    init(@ViewBuilder content: () -> Content) {
        self.content = content()
    }

    var body: some View {
        content
            .padding(Theme.padding)
            .background(AppColors.background)
            .cornerRadius(Theme.cornerRadius)
            .shadow(radius: Theme.shadowRadius)
    }
}
```

## 6. Performance & Best Practices (30 min)

### Efficient View Updates:
- Use `.equatable()` for expensive views
- Extract complex calculations from body
- Leverage `@ViewBuilder` for conditional content

### Modifier Performance Tips:
- Chain modifiers logically
- Avoid unnecessary view recreations
- Use `@ViewBuilder` for complex conditional views

### Testing Custom Modifiers:
```swift
import XCTest
@testable import YourApp

class ModifierTests: XCTestCase {
    func testPrimaryButtonStyle() {
        let button = Button("Test") { }
            .primaryButtonStyle()

        // Test that modifier is applied correctly
        // (In practice, you'd use snapshot testing or view inspection)
    }
}
```

## Practice Exercises

Complete all exercises to master view styling and composition!

