# Sheets & Alerts - Professional UI Presentation

## 1. Introduction to Modal Presentation (30 min)

### What are Sheets?
Sheets are modal views that slide up from the bottom of the screen, perfect for:
- Presenting detailed information
- User input forms
- Settings panels
- Contextual actions

### Key Concepts:
- **Modal Presentation**: Takes focus until dismissed
- **Non-Destructive**: User can cancel or complete action
- **Contextual**: Related to the current screen content

## 2. Basic Sheets Implementation (45 min)

### Simple Sheet Presentation:
```swift
@State private var showingSheet = false

var body: some View {
    Button("Show Sheet") {
        showingSheet = true
    }
    .sheet(isPresented: $showingSheet) {
        DetailView()
    }
}
```

### Sheet with Custom Content:
```swift
.sheet(isPresented: $showSettings) {
    NavigationView {
        SettingsView()
            .navigationTitle("Settings")
            .navigationBarItems(trailing: Button("Done") {
                showSettings = false
            })
    }
}
```

## 3. Advanced Sheet Techniques (60 min)

### Sheets with Data Binding:
```swift
@State private var selectedItem: Item?

var body: some View {
    List(items) { item in
        Text(item.name)
            .onTapGesture {
                selectedItem = item
            }
    }
    .sheet(item: $selectedItem) { item in
        ItemDetailView(item: item)
    }
}
```

### Custom Sheet Detents (iOS 16+):
```swift
.sheet(isPresented: $showSheet) {
    CustomView()
        .presentationDetents([.medium, .large])
        .presentationDragIndicator(.visible)
}
```

### Interactive Dismissal:
```swift
.sheet(isPresented: $showSheet) {
    EditView()
        .interactiveDismissDisabled(hasUnsavedChanges)
}
```

## 4. Full-Screen Cover (30 min)

### When to Use Full-Screen:
- Immersive experiences
- Login screens
- Tutorials
- Major workflow steps

### Implementation:
```swift
@State private var showLogin = false

var body: some View {
    Button("Login") {
        showLogin = true
    }
    .fullScreenCover(isPresented: $showLogin) {
        LoginView()
    }
}
```

## 5. Alert System Fundamentals (45 min)

### Basic Alert Presentation:
```swift
@State private var showAlert = false

var body: some View {
    Button("Delete Item") {
        showAlert = true
    }
    .alert("Confirm Delete", isPresented: $showAlert) {
        Button("Delete", role: .destructive) {
            deleteItem()
        }
        Button("Cancel", role: .cancel) { }
    } message: {
        Text("This action cannot be undone.")
    }
}
```

### Alert with Dynamic Content:
```swift
.alert("Error", isPresented: $showError) {
    Button("OK") { }
} message: {
    Text(errorMessage)
}
```

## 6. Advanced Alert Patterns (60 min)

### Multiple Action Alerts:
```swift
.alert("Choose Action", isPresented: $showActionSheet) {
    Button("Save") { saveDocument() }
    Button("Save As...") { showSaveAs = true }
    Button("Discard", role: .destructive) { discardChanges() }
    Button("Cancel", role: .cancel) { }
} message: {
    Text("What would you like to do with this document?")
}
```

### TextField in Alerts (iOS 15+):
```swift
.alert("Rename Item", isPresented: $showRenameAlert) {
    TextField("New name", text: $newName)
    Button("Rename") { renameItem() }
    Button("Cancel", role: .cancel) { }
} message: {
    Text("Enter a new name for this item")
}
```

## 7. Action Sheets vs Context Menus (30 min)

### Context Menu for Multiple Options:
```swift
Text("File.txt")
    .contextMenu {
        Button("Rename") { showRename = true }
        Button("Duplicate") { duplicateFile() }
        Button("Share") { showShareSheet = true }
        Button("Delete", role: .destructive) { showDeleteAlert = true }
    }
```

## 8. Custom Modal Presentations (40 min)

### Custom Sheet Styles:
```swift
.sheet(isPresented: $showCustomSheet) {
    CustomModalView()
        .background(BackgroundBlurView())
        .cornerRadius(20)
        .shadow(radius: 10)
}
```

### Half-Modal Presentation:
```swift
ZStack {
    // Main content

    if showHalfModal {
        HalfModalView()
            .transition(.move(edge: .bottom))
            .animation(.spring(), value: showHalfModal)
    }
}
```

## 9. State Management for Modals (30 min)

### Centralized Modal State:
```swift
class ModalManager: ObservableObject {
    @Published var activeModal: ActiveModal?

    enum ActiveModal {
        case settings, profile, createPost, search
    }
}

// Usage:
.sheet(item: $modalManager.activeModal) { modal in
    switch modal {
    case .settings: SettingsView()
    case .profile: ProfileView()
    case .createPost: CreatePostView()
    case .search: SearchView()
    }
}
```

## 10. Best Practices & User Experience (30 min)

### When to Use Each Presentation Type:
- **Sheets**: Forms, settings, detailed views
- **Alerts**: Critical information, confirmations
- **Full-Screen Cover**: Major workflow changes
- **Context Menus**: Quick actions on specific items

### Accessibility Considerations:
- Provide clear dismissal options
- Ensure proper focus management
- Support VoiceOver navigation
- Consider reduced motion preferences

## Practice Exercises

Complete all exercises to master modal presentation patterns!

